    "Network service orchestration is therefore required to achieve network autonomy.",
    "Network service orchestration refers to the automated and intelligent integration and coordination of various functions within a network to achieve specific service requirements or service objectives.",
    "It dynamically selects, deploys, and adjusts various functions based on user needs and conditions, thus enabling more efficient, reliable, and flexible network service delivery.",
    "A communication function is required to connect the constructed DTs and network ontology to a physical network, which allocates computing resources and operates the DTN.",
    "Therefore, the NDT requires unified scheduling to map the underlying resources and digital twin function."
